						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Top of the door frame of Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1481.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[40]3, Plava, Mārgas11ira, śu. [7], Saturday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1481, November 27,</hi> the week day being Tuesday and not Saturday.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the completion of a hall <hi rend="italic">(sabhā)</hi> evidently in the temple of Hanumān. It mentions Rāmarasa who perhaps was responsible for this act.</p>						

						</summary>
